There&#39;s a solution involving `MutationObserver`, but it implies that you set the value as a HTML attribute (not via the DOM property):

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    const input = document.getElementById(&#39;input&#39;);

    const observer = new MutationObserver(records =&gt; records.forEach(({
                    attributeName,
                    oldValue,
                    target
                }) =&gt; console.log(`Input attribute ${attributeName} changed from ${oldValue} to ${target.getAttribute(&#39;value&#39;)}`)));
                
    observer.observe(input, {
        attributes: true
    });

    // This programmatically changes the input value and fires a DOM mutation
    input.setAttribute(&#39;value&#39;, &#39;attribute&#39;);

    // This programmatically changes the input value but doesn&#39;t fire a DOM mutation
    input.value = &#39;property&#39;;

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;input id=&quot;input&quot;&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

More details here https://stackoverflow.com/questions/6003819/what-is-the-difference-between-properties-and-attributes-in-html

And also here https://stackoverflow.com/questions/32383349/javascript-use-mutationobserver-to-detect-value-change-in-input-tag

